HEADWORD: Landgraviate
<hw>Land*gra"vi*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>landgraviat</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The territory held by a
landgrave.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The office, jurisdiction, or authority of a
landgrave.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Landgravine</ent>⟦br⟧
